        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18674",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "First off, Zend_Form currently and will always remain agnostic of the request mechanism; you must pass in the data to be validated, plain and simple.\n\nTo implement an isClick() type of functionality *now*, simply use this code:\n\n{code}\n$form->populate($_POST);\nif (null !== $form->getElement('update')->getValue()) {\n}\n{code}\n\nI'm not convinced that an isClicked() method makes a lot of sense knowing that the above will work, but I will continue considering this addition.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-01-29T14:35:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-01-29T14:35:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/19245",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Added this functionality on Monday, 18 Feb 2008 in trunk. You can now populate the form and check what was clicked:\n{code}\n$form->populate($data);\nif ($form->save->isClicked()) {\n    \/\/ 'save' submit was clicked\n}\n{code}\n\nor check it after evaluating:\n{code}\nif ($form->isValid($data)) {\n   if ($form->save->isClicked()) {\n   }\n}\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-19T09:51:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-19T09:51:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36555",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=umpirsky",
                        "name": "umpirsky",
                        "displayName": "Sasa Stamenkovic",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I get:\r\n\r\nZend_Form_Element_Exception: Method isClicked does not exist\r\n\r\nthrown in Zend\\Form\\Element.php on line 931\r\n\r\nwith 1.9.5 version.\r\n\r\nisClicked is not implemented at all?!?\r\n\r\nIs there any other way to check clicked?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=umpirsky",
                        "name": "umpirsky",
                        "displayName": "Sasa Stamenkovic",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-28T11:42:18.000+0000",
